#eNCA Courtesy #DStv43 JOHANNESBURG - The Gauteng Education Department is calling for parents at Leondale High School in Ekurhuleni to enforce discipline at home. The Department says its concerned after a video of the pupils smoking dagga circulated on social media. READ: Over 30 pupils suspended from Joburg school for smoking dagga The Department says it’s also received reports of late coming. Parents of the pupils caught on camera are holding a meeting ahead of the disciplinary hearing on Monday. Watch the video above for more details on this story